A decision by the department of  basic education (DBE) to impose an immediate countrywide suspension on canned pilchards – as part of the national school nutrition menu across all schools in the country – could have a ripple effect on the fishing industry, with at the Oceana Group Limited, which owns the Lucky Star  brand, warning that jobs could be affected. Government’s blanket decision was also bound to have negative brand and huge financial losses, running into millions, according to Zodwa Velleman, Oceana Group Limited executive for regulatory and corporate affairs. Despite the National Regulator for Compulsory Specifications(NRCS) not having...